#Reading in the cleaned data
general_health <- read_csv(here("clean_data/general_health.csv"))
## 
##  Column specification 
## cols(
##   feature_code = col_character(),
##   date_code = col_double(),

##   units = col_character(),
##   value = col_double(),
##   self_assessed_general_health = col_character(),
##   type_of_tenure = col_character(),
##   household_type = col_character(),
##   age = col_character(),
##   gender = col_character(),
##   limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition = col_character()
## )
#Checking for missing values across all columns
general_health %>% 
  summarise(across(.fns = ~sum(is.na(.x))))
#16023 missing dates in date code column
#Show which areas the missing values are coming from
general_health %>% 
  filter(is.na(date_code))
#Checking for unique years in date code column
dates_list <- 
  unique(general_health$date_code)

dates_list
## [1] 2013 2018 2012 2015 2014 2017 2016 2019   NA
#class(dates_list)

#The data ranges from 2012 - 2019
#Checking for unique phrases in limiting condition column
limiting_condition <- 
  unique(general_health$limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition)

limiting_condition
## [1] "All"                   "Limiting condition"    "No limiting condition"
#Changing reponses as follows:-
#Limiting condition = y
#No limiting condition = n
general_health <- general_health %>% 
  mutate(
    limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition = if_else(limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition == "Limiting condition", "Y", limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition),
    limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition = if_else(limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition == "No limiting condition", "N", limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition)
  )
#Checking for unique phrases in self assessment column
self_assessment <- 
  unique(general_health$self_assessed_general_health)

self_assessment
## [1] "Good or Very good" "Fair"              "Bad or Very bad"
#Removing missing values
general_health <- general_health %>% 
  drop_na()
general_health %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Percent") %>%  
    #filtering to remove "All" in limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition column 
  filter(!limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition == "All") %>% 
  select(-household_type, -type_of_tenure, -age, -feature_code, -units) %>% 
  group_by(gender, date_code, value, self_assessed_general_health, limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition) %>% 
  summarise() %>% 
  group_by(date_code, self_assessed_general_health, limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition) %>% 
  summarise(mean_self_assessment_value = mean(value)) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_col(aes(x = limiting_long_term_physical_or_mental_health_condition, y = mean_self_assessment_value, fill = self_assessed_general_health)) +
  facet_grid(~date_code) +
  labs(title = "Self Assessed General Health in Scotland",
       subtitle = "2012 - 2019",
       x = "Limiting Long Term Physical or Mental Health Condition",
       y = "Mean Self Assessment Value",
       fill = "Self Assessed General Health") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) 
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'gender', 'date_code', 'value', 'self_assessed_general_health' (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'date_code', 'self_assessed_general_health' (override with `.groups` argument)

general_health_limiting_conditions_all <- general_health %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Percent") %>%  
  select(-household_type, -type_of_tenure, -age, -feature_code, -units) %>% 
  group_by(gender, date_code, value, self_assessed_general_health) %>% 
  summarise() %>% 
  filter(gender == "All") %>% 
  group_by(date_code, self_assessed_general_health) %>% 
  summarise(mean_self_assessment_value = mean(value)) 
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'gender', 'date_code', 'value' (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'date_code' (override with `.groups` argument)
ggplot(general_health_limiting_conditions_all, aes(x = date_code, y = mean_self_assessment_value, colour = self_assessed_general_health)) +
    geom_line() +
     labs(title = "Self Assessed General Health in Scotland",
       subtitle = "2012 - 2019",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Mean Self Assessment Value",
       colour = "Self Assessment") +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(2012:2019)) 

general_health_limiting_conditions_male <- general_health %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Percent") %>% 
  select(-household_type, -type_of_tenure, -age, -feature_code, -units) %>% 
  group_by(gender, date_code, measurement, value) %>% 
  summarise() %>% 
  filter(gender == "Male") %>% 
  group_by(date_code) %>% 
  summarise(mean_self_assessment_value = mean(value))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'gender', 'date_code', 'measurement' (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
general_health_limiting_conditions_female <- general_health %>% 
  filter(measurement == "Percent") %>% 
  select(-household_type, -type_of_tenure, -age, -feature_code, -units) %>% 
  group_by(gender, date_code, measurement, value) %>% 
  summarise() %>% 
  filter(gender == "Female") %>% 
  group_by(date_code) %>% 
  summarise(mean_self_assessment_value = mean(value))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'gender', 'date_code', 'measurement' (override with `.groups` argument)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
  ggplot(general_health_limiting_conditions_male, aes(x = date_code, y = mean_self_assessment_value)) +
    geom_line() +
  geom_line(aes(colour = "Male")) +
    geom_line(data =general_health_limiting_conditions_female, aes(colour = "Female")) +
     labs(title = "Self Assessed General Health in Scotland by Gender",
       subtitle = "2012 - 2019",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Mean Self Assessment Value",
       colour = "Gender") +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(2012:2019))
